<file xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its" xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:qh5="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiv2p2_html5_v1p0" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <sharedstimuli>
        <sharedstimulus id="assets/d67a0fbc638e6f66705e1/passage NEW.xml">
            <label key="03309daffd806c305cd8702b39f1d027">
                <text>Noise Pollution</text>
            </label>
            <label key="417e89119d44a9e9ecd4ab0b510e9c14">
                <text>Marine animals produce and respond to a wide variety of sounds to search for food, communicate, find mating partners, avoid predators and navigate.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="080c45d2f6c2151990b0782c19e409f8">
                <text>Rain, waves, surf, underwater earthquakes and volcanoes, and icebergs breaking and colliding, all make noises in the sea.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="b8ae18c9bde62447b85b9be6b011bfc5">
                <text>Humans are increasingly contributing to noise in the sea. This happens during shipping, exploration for raw materials, military activities, and the construction and operation of wind turbines and drilling platforms.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="2de2ca34aa09b4739a276d5d3172ab78">
                <text>These activities change the noises in the sea, which can scare marine animals and disturb their behaviours.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="581c3345795b64dcb218f7af5291df71">
                <text>The map shows the world’s major shipping routes.</text>
            </label>
        </sharedstimulus>
        <sharedstimulus id="assets/85eae803638e7d4ee6352/passage NEW 1.xml">
            <label key="03309daffd806c305cd8702b39f1d027">
                <text>Noise Pollution</text>
            </label>
            <label key="11411a486f05cd8bd4e4f11ebc8f1cc2">
                <text>Echolocation is the techniques that some animals use to navigate through their environments and to locate objects.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="32fab66a79dc3165c4c3d5c81f3b9498">
                <text>Animals using echolocation emit sounds that are reflected by the objects around them. The echoes provide the animals with information about the distance and direction of the objects.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="54272ae3491897a6bdf3445976e87011">
                <text>This formula is used to calculate the distance travelled by the sound waves used in echolocation:</text>
            </label>
            <label key="d04a3af610036b449ac34b0dbea3f0c4">
                <text>In this formula:</text>
            </label>
            <label key="996821fce995e834c68bd53a4d2c3245">
                <text><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><m:mi>d</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:annotation encoding="latex">d</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> (m) is the distance between the transmitter (animal emitting the sound) and the target object</text>
            </label>
            <label key="23372ab9c756454a0cc885d82c568dfa">
                <text><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><m:mi>v</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:annotation encoding="latex">v</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> (m/s) is the speed of sound</text>
            </label>
            <label key="bd5fe43d4629ad0e6a22fe25ed314b0c">
                <text><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:annotation encoding="latex">t</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the time it takes for the sound waves to travel to the target and back to the transmitter.</text>
            </label>
        </sharedstimulus>
    </sharedstimuli>
    <items>
        <item id="i638e7ba65101215016b6982740b6723560">
            <label key="ed5414084c451f5ac62bd83394ad2381">
                <text>Do the statements in the table describe risks of noise pollution for marine animals?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="a8c38cd5723dd799a00d4ac84d71561e">
                <text>Select ‘Yes’ or ‘No’ for each statement.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="fdc1563a8afc5411a7aba3beeb918bd4">
                <text>
                    <strong>‌Yes‌</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="758eaa648d8250f58a4ec4251f2ea215">
                <text>
                    <strong>‌No‌</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="229d4792dd2c6d1cd85b8048a08661c0">
                <text>Animals may flee from the noise and leave their natural environment.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="4b850e21a740dc3262c2244296512b64">
                <text>Animals that use echolocation can no longer find food.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="2243e6a691bd3af8ecfa6b27cb90c2d6">
                <text>Noise pollution makes it difficult for whales to communicate, navigate and find mating partners.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="7d0196aa6f265a2cd39aba97453ffd9b">
                <text>Fish have problems absorbing oxygen if there is too much noise.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i638e7c30e536f12766550c1c1ef5975417">
            <label key="842a03c273149048b12e62243825548c">
                <text>Would the actions in the table reduce noise pollution in the sea?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="bc3e728acece219ebd37214b9177c916">
                <text>Select ‘Yes’ or ‘No’ for each action.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="fdc1563a8afc5411a7aba3beeb918bd4">
                <text>
                    <strong>‌Yes‌</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="758eaa648d8250f58a4ec4251f2ea215">
                <text>
                    <strong>‌No‌</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="dd22ac4bb558793dbc6e17d16fc56bf3">
                <text>Decrease the maximum speed for ships.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="3ab19ff72df841ee88f263f86edfd205">
                <text>Increase the number of cruise ships to spread the noise evenly.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="76278f7798d54eac263f38bc385dba53">
                <text>Establish noise-exclusion zones.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="8db72a6623f76a15e37e7195037920f2">
                <text>Use alternative shipping routes that avoid sensitive natural environments.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i638e83ddb923043617368d419e3eecded8">
            <label key="123a394241df950f8ae7df1c4e3b59bd">
                <text>Explain why the number ‘2’ is used in the formula for calculating the distance travelled by sound waves in echolocation.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
    </items>
